I_{n} = \int_0^1 \frac{x^{n-1}}{2-x} dx
n=1,2,3,\ldots
x^n = x^{n-1} (2-(2-x))
I_{n+1} = 2I_n - \frac{1}{n} 
I_{n+1}-2I_n=\int_0^1\frac{x^{n}-2x^{n-1}}{2-x}dx=-\int_0^1\frac{x^{n-1}(2-x)}{2-x}dx=-\int_0^1 x^{n-1}dx\text{ as }2-x\ne0
\int x^m dx=\begin{cases} \ln x &\mbox{if } m =-1 \\  \frac{x^{m+1}}{m+1}& \mbox{else where }\end{cases}
